From a0bc3993a95fca01f59e2f09bf466b3955aaeee8 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Kol Crooks <kol.crooks@datadoghq.com>
Date: Fri, 8 May 2026 14:14:32 -0400
Subject: [PATCH] Phase 10 Batch 3: reply-to-comment threading
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

Native review threads now expose a Reply input while a draft is open
(`canReply: true` on threads that have at least one server-side parent).
A typed reply lands in the draft alongside top-level comments, tagged
with the GitHub database id of the earliest comment on the line.

Submit splits the draft into two passes:
- new top-level threads + the review verdict (Approve / Comment /
  Request Changes) ride the existing
  `/repos/{o}/{r}/pulls/{n}/reviews` batch.
- replies POST individually to
  `/repos/{o}/{r}/pulls/{n}/comments` with `in_reply_to` (the reviews
  endpoint rejects `in_reply_to` inside its `comments` payload, so
  replies don't fit into the same batch).

`KrtReviewDraftComment.inReplyTo` carries the parent id; the storage
envelope is forward-compatible (older drafts without the field still
load — `inReplyTo` defaults to `undefined`).
---
